<br>
With normal melees, they can switch sides when she nears a wall, and push the other way.  A pet group would have a difficult time getting pets off of her, then on the other side of her.  It could be done, in theory, but considering her AoEs, backing the pets off would be difficult at best.<br>
<br>
Plus that assumes that the pets won't get feared.<br>
<br>
Still, it would be interesting to try non-conventional groups vs. Vox.  Right now, Tunare has a dragon database, and weekly dragon raids that are coordinated with the server board.  Every week is the same thing - 8 to 10 groups of lvl 44-52 peeps going in to get raid credit and a chance at seniority for the ND loot.  The first 4 groups are always the same, with monk pullers, pallys, and cleric.  The rest of the casters get dumped in the group 5+.  It was fun at first, but there is no challenge to it at all. <p><div align="center"> <a href="#"><img src="http://www.nemeandesign.net/eq/sig2.jpg" width="382" height="66" border="0" onClick="window.open('http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=528641', 'morillion', 'WIDTH=800,HEIGHT=600')"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 399<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/03 2:03:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=439.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Storytime</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>No two magicians epic or no epic can take down Vox, however one gropu of lv 60 people could likely do it if it was possible to engage her without getting banished.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
